            <fr:title text="Characterization of positivity in terms of partial elements">Characterization of positivity in terms of partial elements</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="jms-001S.xml" title="Pointed dcpo" addr="jms-001S" type="local">pointed</fr:link> dcpo. Then an element <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a:A]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="jms-001M.xml" title="The positive elements of a pointed dcpo" addr="jms-001M" type="local">positive</fr:link> if and only if for any partial element <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u: LA]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\sqsubseteq \bigsqcup _{p:u{\downarrow }}u[p]]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u{\downarrow }=\top ]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
